00137 /*
00138  * REGISTER_MIB(): This macro simply loads register_mib with less pain:
00139  * 
00140  * descr:   A short description of the mib group being loaded.
00141  * var:     The variable structure to load.
00142  * vartype: The variable structure used to define it (variable[2, 4, ...])
00143  * theoid:  An *initialized* *exact length* oid pointer.
00144  *          (sizeof(theoid) *must* return the number of elements!) 
00145  */
00146 
00147 #define REGISTER_MIB(descr, var, vartype, theoid)                      \
00148   if (register_mib(descr, (struct variable *) var, sizeof(struct vartype), \
00149                sizeof(var)/sizeof(struct vartype),                     \
00150                theoid, sizeof(theoid)/sizeof(oid)) != MIB_REGISTERED_OK ) \
00151         DEBUGMSGTL(("register_mib", "%s registration failed\n", descr));
00152
